Since podman also uses existing credentials in these files by default (for docker e.g. `${HOME}/.docker/config.json`), module execution will fail if a docker login exists for the registry specified in any `authfile` is used by podman. This can be ignored by setting `ignore_docker_credentials` to `yes` - the credentials will be kept and `changed` will be false.
